1. *Predstave* su odličan način da se upozna nova kultura. (Nouns: "Predstave" - "Performances" / Translation: "Performances are a great way to get to know a new culture.")
2. Želim da *predstavim* svog prijatelja Petru svima vama. (Verb: "Predstavim" - "Introduce" / Translation: "I want to introduce my friend Peter to all of you.")
3. *Predstavljajući* svoju kompaniju, dala sam naglasak na inovativnost. (Verb, Present Participle: "Predstavljajući" - "Presenting" / Translation: "Presenting my company, I emphasized innovation.")
4. *Predstavljena* je nova linija proizvoda na sajmu. (Verb, Passive Voice: "Predstavljena" - "Presented" / Translation: "The new product line was presented at the fair.")
5. Uloge u *predstavi* su bile odlično odigrane. (Noun: "Predstavi" - "Play" / Translation: "The roles in the play were excellently performed.")
6. Učesnici su imali zadatak da *predstave* svoje ideje u roku od pet minuta. (Verb: "Predstave" - "Present" / Translation: "Participants were tasked with presenting their ideas within five minutes.")
7. *Predstavništvo* ove kompanije nalazi se u centru grada. (Noun: "Predstavništvo" - "Representation" / Translation: "The representation of this company is located in the city center.")
8. On je *predstavnik* kompanije za Balkan region. (Noun: "Predstavnik" - "Representative" / Translation: "He is a representative of the company for the Balkan region.")
9. *Predstava* počinje u 20 časova. (Noun: "Predstava" - "Performance" / Translation: "The performance starts at 8 PM.")
10. Ova knjiga je *predstavljena* kao najprodavanija na Sajmu knjiga. (Verb: "Predstavljena" - "Presented" / Translation: "This book was presented as the best-selling at the Book Fair.")